results.name: Number of divisors of n whose binary representation is contained in that of n.
comment: a(n)>1 for n>1; a(p) =2 for primes p.
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
Index entries for sequences related to binary expansion of n
example: n=18: divisors of 18: 1='1', 2='10', 3='11', 6='110', 9='1001' and 18='10010': four of them are binary substrings of '10010', therefore a(18) =4.
program: a093640 n  = length [d | d <- [1..n], mod n d == 0,
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Apr 07 2004
